to the editor re american prudery and its opposite op ed feb 19 by richard marusa while a general acceptance of more nudity in advertising may in itself be reasonable in practice the burden falls predominantly on women 's bodies a relaxation of nudity standards would only worsen the already unequal representation of the female body which is usually the unclothed one such imagery undermines the equality of women in democratic societies european practice may seem liberated but in fact it is repressive and oppressive theirs is the old world view ours is the new thomas starr cambridge mass feb 21 2000 the writer is an assistant professor of graphic design at northeastern university

